column1: # - R1: oligo_rc + UMI_rc + LigEven + OddTop1 + LigOdd + EvenTop1 + LigEven + OddTop2 + LigOdd + EvenTop2 + LigEven + OddTop3 + LigOdd + NYLigOddStgTop
# - R2: NYStgBot + Odd + OddBot3 + Even + EvenBot2 + Odd + OddBot2 + Even + EvenBot1 + Odd + OddBot1 + Even + UMI + oligo
# - A read length of 156 nt is required to span (assuming no indels) the entire structure shown above (aka "DNA insert") between the Illumina sequencing primers.
# - This config as-is assumes read lengths of >= 156 nt from each orientation; delete groups as appropriate for shorter read lengths.
# - The last nucleotide was dropped from each OddBot1 tag so that the detected tag (which allows for a Levenshtein distance of 1) does not eat into the subsequent Even tag.

# - The antibody ID tag group in Read 1 is named "oligo_rc" because Read 1 contains the reverse complement sequence of the antibody ID, relative to the 5'-3' orientation of the antibody ID in the single-stranded oligo.
# - The oligo tags are named BEAD_<target>_<antibody>.
# - The edit distances here are appropriate if all 96 tags are used in each round; more flexible edit distances may be allowed if only a subset of tags are used in each round.
# - Output sequences should be empty strings due to the trimming specified by the 'right' column.
# Splitcode command: splitcode -c config.tsv --nFastqs=2 --assign --no-outb --no-x-out --mapping=/dev/null --x-names --mod-names --output=out1.fasta.gz,out2.fasta.gz R1.fastq.gz R2.fastq.gz
# - use --mod-names to add barcode to read name
# - use --x-names to add UMI as a SAM tag: RX:Z:<read 1 UMI, reverse-complemented>-<read 2 UMI>; any differences between <read 1 UMI, reverse-complemented> and <read 2 UMI> reflect sequencing errors.
